[<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B7">7</xref>].</p></table-wrap-foot></table-wrap><p>Coverage is not homogeneous across the risk categories, with higher risk categories being characterized by comparatively better coverage. For example, for populations at high and very high risk, coverage is estimated at 48, 77 and 87% for the travel time thresholds of 1, 3 and 5 hours respectively. These percentages decrease for moderate and for low and very low risk categories &#x02013; the health systems deploying better equipped facilities and skilled staff in areas where transmission of the disease is more intense.</p><p>Full details for a range of travel-times, for all study countries and for all risk categories are provided in Additional file
